org.omnaest.utils.beans.mapconverter
Class BeanToNestedMapConverter<B>

java.lang.Object
  org.omnaest.utils.beans.mapconverter.BeanToNestedMapConverter<B>

public class BeanToNestedMapConverter<B>
extends Object

A BeanToNestedMapConverter marshalls a given JavaBean into a Map or unmarshalls a given Map into a JavaBean. This process is transitive and allows to translate arbitrary object graphs into nested Maps.

With #setPropertyAccessType(PropertyAccessType) it can be declared in which way the BeanToNestedMapConverter should access given JavaBeans. With the default value of BeanPropertyAccessor.PropertyAccessType.PROPERTY the BeanToNestedMapConverter will only use getters and setters whereby with BeanPropertyAccessor.PropertyAccessType.FIELD the fields of the JavaBeans are accessed directly ignoring any getters or setters.

Author:
Omnaest
